solutions.content:
Well, I am not much expert in DP, just got enthusiastic and interested in learning DSA for last 5-6 months or so. After some practice in DP, I was very confident. So, when I saw the question I tried to design DP table and try to build a formula, but that cooldown time condition always pushed me back to think from beginning, so finally decided to go in old school way, i.e. to think of a recursive approach first by intuition, then definitely top-down/bottom-up gonna be piece of cake.
So, here how I thought of it -
lets d1 and d2 be the days of buying and selling stock respectively (obs. d1 < d2), now have following things to consider:
1. if price on d1 is less than price on d2, then
	profit at d2 = prices[d2] - prices[d1] + (profit on the days which are greater than d2 + cooldown)
2. Okay, so even we can sell the stock on the other day if it can bring more profit.
3. if price on d1 is greater than price on d2, then,
		we will take next day of d1 and restart the process. Here, someone can argue that why don't we choose another day to sell when stock price is more. Well, this condition is already covered in step 2, so we will pick next buying day instead.

So, here's the recursive sudo code (assuming recursive function getMaxProfit(buyIdx, sellIdx)):
if(prices[buyIdx] < prices[sellIdx]):
	maxProfit = max of {prices[sellIdx] - prices[buyIdx] + getMaxProfit(sellIdx + 2, sellIdx + 3)[if we sell stock on sellIdx, next transaction must happen from index **sellIdx + 2** (next to sellIdx + **1** for cooldown]} and {getMaxProfit(buyIdx, sellIdx + 1)} (condition 1, 2)
else:
maxProfit = getMaxProfit(buyIdx + 1, buyIdx + 2) (condition 3)

Complete Code:
```
int getMaxProfit(int[] prices, int bIdx, int sIdx){        
        if(bIdx >= prices.length || sIdx >= prices.length) return 0; 
        if(prices[sIdx] > prices[bIdx])
            return Math.max(prices[sIdx] - prices[bIdx] + 
                                  getMaxProfit(prices, sIdx + 2, sIdx + 3), 
                                  getMaxProfit(prices, bIdx, sIdx + 1));
        else
            return getMaxProfit(prices, bIdx + 1, bIdx + 2);    
    }
```
Now, if the solution is correct it will definitely throw TLE, as runtime complexity is exponential - O(2^n). Well it did so but made me happy, as memoization approach is opened after that -
```
int getMaxProfit(int[] prices, int bIdx, int sIdx, int[][] memo){        
        if(bIdx >= prices.length || sIdx >= prices.length) return 0;        
        if(memo[bIdx][sIdx] != 0) return memo[bIdx][sIdx];
        if(prices[sIdx] > prices[bIdx])
            memo[bIdx][sIdx] = Math.max(prices[sIdx] - prices[bIdx] + 
                                  getMaxProfit(prices, sIdx + 2, sIdx + 3, memo), 
                                  getMaxProfit(prices, bIdx, sIdx + 1, memo));
        else
            memo[bIdx][sIdx] = getMaxProfit(prices, bIdx + 1, bIdx + 2, memo);

        return memo[bIdx][sIdx];
    }
```
Awesome, so we have our O(n) runtime working solution. So, lets take it further and build our bottom-up solution:
```
		int[][] dp = new int[prices.length][prices.length];
        for(int i = dp.length - 2; i >= 0; i--){
            for(int j = dp.length - 1; j > i; j--){
                if(prices[j] > prices[i])
                    dp[i][j] = Math.max(dpUtil(dp, i, j + 1), 
                                        prices[j] - prices[i] + dpUtil(dp, j + 2, j + 3));
                else
                    dp[i][j] = dpUtil(dp, i + 1, i + 2);
            }
        }        
        return dp[0][1];
```
where dpUtil is to check valid index -
```
int dpUtil(int[][] dp, int i, int j){
        if(i >= dp.length || j >= dp.length) return 0;
        return dp[i][j];
    }
```

**Note:** We can sell from index 1 only, hence dp[0][1] will have our final answer.

Full working code:
```
class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {
        if(prices.length < 2) return 0;
        //-----Bottom-Up DP start-----
        int[][] dp = new int[prices.length][prices.length];
        for(int i = dp.length - 2; i >= 0; i--){
            for(int j = dp.length - 1; j > i; j--){
                if(prices[j] > prices[i])
                    dp[i][j] = Math.max(dpUtil(dp, i, j + 1), 
                                        prices[j] - prices[i] + dpUtil(dp, j + 2, j + 3));
                else
                    dp[i][j] = dpUtil(dp, i + 1, i + 2);
            }
        }        
        return dp[0][1];
        //-----Bottom-Up DP end------

        //int[][] memo = new int[prices.length][prices.length];
        //return getMaxProfit(prices, 0, 1, memo);
    }

    //Check whether index is valid
    int dpUtil(int[][] dp, int i, int j){
        if(i >= dp.length || j >= dp.length) return 0;
        return dp[i][j];
    }

    //Top-Down DP
    int getMaxProfit(int[] prices, int bIdx, int sIdx, int[][] memo){        
        if(bIdx >= prices.length || sIdx >= prices.length) return 0;        
        if(memo[bIdx][sIdx] != 0) return memo[bIdx][sIdx];
