solutions.content:
# Intuition
First I have solved the problem with normal recursive method. Later on I have used dp to reduce the time complexity. 

# Approach
In the question it is clearly given that you can buy and sell the stocks multiple times but there is cool down time.

So we take two things into consideration. 
1) Whether a stock is bought.
2) Cool Down Time.

Let us make a flag variable which determines whether we hold a stock. If we hold the stock flag is 1 else it is 0. 

If we do not hold a stack, we have two ways either buy the stock or just do not buy. We need to pick the maximum from both the cases. In the case considering that you buy the stock update the flag as 1. As you buy the stoct your money is debited so we subtract the money. In the case considering that you donot buy the stock update nothing.

If we do hold a stack, we have two ways either sell the stock or just do not sell. We need to pick the maximum from both the cases. In the case considering that you sell the stock update the flag as 0 but if we sell the stock we need to wait for one day to be cooled down so we update idx to idx+2 after selling the stock. As you sell the stoct your money is credited so we add the money. In the case considering that you donot sell the stock update nothing.

The terminating Case would be index is greater than size.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
 O(2^N) for normal recursion
 O(N) for dp method

- Space complexity:
 O(N)

# Code
```
//Normal recursive method

class Solution {
public:
int soln(vector<int>&prices,int idx,int flag){
    if(idx>=prices.size()){
        return 0;
    }
    int ans = INT_MIN;
    if(!flag){
        ans = max(ans,soln(prices,idx+1,1)-prices[idx]);
        ans = max(ans,soln(prices,idx+1,0));
    }else{
        ans = max(ans,soln(prices,idx+2,0)+prices[idx]);
        ans = max(ans,soln(prices,idx+1,1));
    }
    return ans;
}
    int maxProfit(vector<int>& prices) {
        return soln(prices,0,0);
    }
};

//Using dp

class Solution {
public:
int soln(vector<vector<int>>&dp,vector<int>&prices,int idx,int flag){
    if(idx>=prices.size()){
        return 0;
    }
    if(dp[idx][flag] != -1){
        return dp[idx][flag];
    }
    int ans = INT_MIN;
    if(!flag){
        ans = max(ans,soln(dp,prices,idx+1,1)-prices[idx]);
        ans = max(ans,soln(dp,prices,idx+1,0));
    }else{
        ans = max(ans,soln(dp,prices,idx+2,0)+prices[idx]);
        ans = max(ans,soln(dp,prices,idx+1,1));
    }
    return dp[idx][flag] = ans;
}
    int maxProfit(vector<int>& prices) {
        vector<vector<int>>dp(prices.size(),vector<int>(2,-1));
        return soln(dp,prices,0,0);
    }
};
```

