int maxProfit(vector<int>& prices) {
	const int n = prices.size();
	int empty = 0, hold = INT_MIN, cooldown = 0;
	for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
		tie(empty, hold, cooldown) = make_tuple(max(empty, cooldown), max(hold, empty - prices[i]), hold + prices[i]);
	return max(empty, cooldown);
}
```

The idea is just state machine.
To become `empty` today, you either were `empty` yesterday, or you were `cooldown` and turned `empty` today.
To become `hold` today, you either were `hold` yesterday, or you buy today.
To become `cooldown` today, you have to sell today.

