solutions.content:
For each day, there are 3 kinds of state: rest, hold, sold.

At the first day, we are at rest state, then the other day we have 2 choices:
	1. not buy stock => rest state 
	2. buy stock => hold state

If we are in hold state, then the other day we have 2 choices:
	1. not sell stock => hold state
	2. sell stock => sold state

If we are in sold state, the other day we have only one choice, that is rest (since we must cool down after selling).

So:
i in range (1, prices.length)
hold[i] = max(hold[i-1], rest[i-1]-prices[i-1])
rest[i] = max(rest[i-1], sold[i-1])
sold[i] = hold[i-1] + prices[i-1]

```
class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {
        int day = prices.length+1;
        int rest[] = new int[day];
        int hold[] = new int[day];
        int sold[] = new int[day];

        rest[0] = 0;
        sold[0] = 0;
        hold[0] = Integer.MIN_VALUE;

        for(int i=1;i<day;i++){
            sold[i] = hold[i-1]+prices[i-1];
            rest[i] = Math.max(rest[i-1],sold[i-1]);
            hold[i] = Math.max(hold[i-1],rest[i-1]-prices[i-1]);
        }

		//hold[day-1] must be smaller than rest[day-1]
        return Math.max(rest[day-1],sold[day-1]);
    }
}
```

