solutions.content:
[🎨 The ART of Dynamic Programming](https://leetcode.com/discuss/general-discussion/712010/The-ART-of-Dynamic-Programming-An-Intuitive-Approach%3A-from-Apprentice-to-Master)

1. **A**ll possibilities are considered via top-down brute-force depth-first-search
2. **R**emember each subproblem's optimal solution via a DP memo
3. **T**urn the top-down solution upside-down to create the bottom-up solution

Note: similar to [714. Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock with Transaction Fee](https://leetcode.com/problems/best-time-to-buy-and-sell-stock-with-transaction-fee/discuss/1586778/The-ART-of-Dynamic-Programming), this is one of the most difficult DP problems to "turn upside down", since we are *not* following the recursive stack unwinding.  Instead the bottom-up solution tracks previous best states to formulate current best states per the following state machine.

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/eea00a68-0964-4531-a75f-114b7ac1bb3e_1636394391.5816202.png)

`none` = we do *not* `have` any stock, so we can either hold or buy
`have` = we own the stock we `have` bought, so we can either hold or sell
`sold` = we sold the stock we `have` bought, so we must cooldown (ie. go to `none` for at least 1 turn)

---

**Kotlin Solutions:**
1. **A**ll possibilities are considered via top-down brute-force depth-first-search
```
class Solution {
    fun maxProfit(A: IntArray, NONE: Int = -1): Int {
        var N = A.size
        fun go(i: Int = 0, have: Int = NONE): Int {
            if (N <= i)
                return 0
            var buy  = if (have == NONE) go(i + 1, A[i]) else 0
            var sell = if (have != NONE) go(i + 2, NONE) + A[i] - have else 0
            var hold = go(i + 1, have)
            return listOf(buy, sell, hold).max()!!
        }
        return go()
    }
}
```

2. **R**emember each subproblem's optimal solution via a DP memo
```
class Solution {
    fun maxProfit(A: IntArray, NONE: Int = -1): Int {
        var N = A.size
        var m = mutableMapOf<String, Int>()
        fun go(i: Int = 0, have: Int = NONE): Int {
            if (N <= i)
                return 0
            var k = "$i,$have"
            if (!m.contains(k)) {
                var buy  = if (have == NONE) go(i + 1, A[i]) else 0
                var sell = if (have != NONE) go(i + 2, NONE) + A[i] - have else 0
                var hold = go(i + 1, have)
                m[k] = listOf(buy, sell, hold).max()!!
            }
            return m[k]!!
        }
        return go()
    }
}
```

3. **T**urn the top-down solution upside-down to create the bottom-up solution
```
class Solution {
    fun maxProfit(A: IntArray, INF: Int = 1001): Int {
        var N = A.size
        var none = IntArray(N + 1) { 0 }
        var have = IntArray(N + 1) { 0 }
        var sold = IntArray(N + 1) { 0 }
        have[0] = -INF  // to consider buy for A[0]
        for (i in 1..N) {
            var x = A[i - 1]
            none[i] = Math.max(none[i - 1], sold[i - 1])      // implicit hold when none[i] = none[i - 1]
            have[i] = Math.max(have[i - 1], none[i - 1] - x)  // implicit hold when have[i] = have[i - 1], -x because we buy at price x
            sold[i] = have[i - 1] + x                         // +x because we sell at price x
        }
        return listOf(none[N], have[N], sold[N]).max()!!
    }
}
```

4. Memory optimization O(N) 👉 O(1) since we only need the previous solutions to formulate current solutions
```
data class State(var none: Int, var have: Int, var sold: Int)
class Solution {
    fun maxProfit(A: IntArray, INF: Int = 1001): Int {
        var N = A.size
        var cur = State(0, -INF, 0)  // have = -INF to consider buy for A[0]
        for (x in A) {
            var pre = State(cur.none, cur.have, cur.sold)
            cur.none = Math.max(pre.none, pre.sold)      // implicit hold when none[i] = none[i - 1]
            cur.have = Math.max(pre.have, pre.none - x)  // implicit hold when have[i] = have[i - 1], -x because we buy at price x
            cur.sold = pre.have + x                      // +x because we sell at price x
        }
        return listOf(cur.none, cur.have, cur.sold).max()!!
    }
}
```

