solutions.content:
# Method#1
Using Naive way to brute force all the possibility.
Recursion Tree will have n level due to n business date to trade.
Each branch in each level will split into 3 new branch with operations: buy, sell and nothing.
Time Complexity: O(n^3)
Space Complexity: O(n)

# Method#2
Using Dynamic Programming to Solve this question. 
Before using DP, we should clarify 4 things: State, Target, Base Case and Algorithm/Transfer State.

1. State
hold[i]: the maximum profit to hold stock at position/date i
unhold[]: the maximum profit to unhold stock at position/date i

2. Target
return unhold[n - 1]

3. Base Case
unhold[0] = 0
hold[0]   = -profit[0]

4. Algorithm / Transfer State
unhold[i] has two option at date i:
    a. Sell the stock: unhold[i] = hold[i - 1] + profit[i]
    b. Have no stock:  unhold[i] = unhold[i - 1]
hold[i] has two option at date i:
    a. Buy the stock:  hold[i] = unhold[i - 2] - profit[i]
    b. Keep the stock: hold[i] = hold[i - 1]

```
class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {
        if(prices.length <= 1){
            return 0;
        }
        int n = prices.length;
        int[] unhold = new int[n];
        int[] hold = new int[n];
        hold[0] = -1 * prices[0];
        for(int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            unhold[i] = Math.max(hold[i - 1] + prices[i], unhold[i - 1]);
            if(i == 1) {
                hold[i] = Math.max(unhold[0] - prices[1], hold[0]);
            } else {
                hold[i] = Math.max(unhold[i - 2] - prices[i], hold[i - 1]);
            }
        }
        return unhold[n - 1];
    }
}
```
Example:
[1,2,3,0,2]
unhold: 0   1   2   2   3 <- TargetValue
hold  :-1  -1  -1   1  whatever

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)


# Improve Method#2
Improve the space complexity by using only 4 variables.

```
class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {
        if(prices.length <= 1){
            return 0;
        }
        int n = prices.length;
        int unhold0 = 0, hold0 = -1 * prices[0];
        int unhold1 = Math.max(hold0 + prices[1], unhold0), hold1 = Math.max(unhold0 - prices[1], hold0);
        for(int i = 2; i < n; i++) {
            int prevUnhold1 = unhold1, prevHold1 = hold1;
            unhold1 = Math.max(hold1 + prices[i], unhold1);
            hold1 = Math.max(unhold0 - prices[i], hold1);

            unhold0 = prevUnhold1;
            hold0 = prevHold1;
        }
        return unhold1;
    }
}
```

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

