solutions.content:
**The nodes having more edges attached to it will be our answer.
In other words the nodes having highest indegree will be the answer.
If you remember the topological sort order, then the last nodes in topological order have highest indegree
There can be either 1 node or 2 node as root.**


**Algorithm -**

1. Create a graph with adjacency list
2. Create an indegree array to store indegree of the nodes, initialise indegree array with 0
3. if number of nodes is 1, return {0}
4. Create vector<int> ans to return answer
5. if number of nodes are 2, return {0,1}
6. Fill the edges in graph and store the indegree of nodes in indegree array
7. Create a queue to perform BFS
8. Store all leaf nodes in queue, (leaf nodes are those nodes which have indegree as 1
9. Traversing the graph level order according to 1 indegree nodes
10. For each level, s = q.size() and clear to stored answer as if there are elements in queue then we will have our answer in that queue(in topological sort, most indegree node will be the final answer)
11. For all nodes of that level, (watch s-- loop in code), pop them from queue, push it to our ans and treverse all adjacent nodes of the popped node and decrease their indegree by 1, if indegree of that adjacent node is 1 we will push it to our queue
12. return ans finally

```
 vector<int> findMinHeightTrees(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        vector<vector<int>> graph(n); 
        int indegree[n];
        memset(indegree, 0 , sizeof(indegree));
        if(n == 1){
            return {0};
        }

        if(n == 2){
            return {0,1};
        }

        for(vector<int> edge: edges){
            graph[edge[0]].push_back(edge[1]);
            graph[edge[1]].push_back(edge[0]);
            indegree[edge[0]] += 1;              // storing indegree of nodes
            indegree[edge[1]] += 1;              // storing indegree of nodes
        }

        queue<int> q;

        for(int i = 0 ; i < n ; i++ ){
            if(indegree[i] == 1){
                q.push(i);                       // storing leaf nodes in queue
            }
        }
        vector<int> ans;

        while( q.empty()  == false){
            int s =  q.size();                  // getting number of nodes on a particular level of graph
            ans = {};
            while(s--){                         // traversing all nodes on that level
                int u = q.front();
                q.pop();
                ans.push_back(u);

                for(int adj : graph[u]){           // traversing the adjacent nodes of the popped node
                    indegree[adj] -= 1;           // decreasing the indegree of adjacent node by 1
                    if(indegree[adj] == 1){
                        q.push(adj);                   // storing 1 indegree node in queue, there will be some having negative and 0, we need to skip them we have to store only 1 indegree nodes, which shows that this node is a leaf if it is detached from its parent
                    }
                }

            }
        }

        return ans;

    }
```




