### Steps:
* build graph using HashMap and build inDegrees array
* use BFS, start visiting from all vertices with inDegree = 1
* the last existing vertices with inDegree == 1 are the result

```
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> findMinHeightTrees(int n, int[][] edges) {
        List<Integer> result = new ArrayList();
        int[] inDegree = new int[n];

        if (n == 1) {
            result.add(0);
            return result;
        }

        //build graph map, and count number of indegrees for each vertex:
        Map<Integer, List<Integer>> map = new HashMap();
        for (int[] pair: edges) {
            if (!map.containsKey(pair[0])) 
                map.put(pair[0], new ArrayList());

            if (!map.containsKey(pair[1])) 
                map.put(pair[1], new ArrayList());

            map.get(pair[0]).add(pair[1]);
            map.get(pair[1]).add(pair[0]);

            inDegree[pair[0]]++;
            inDegree[pair[1]]++;
        }

        //add all singly connected vertices
        Queue<Integer> queue = new LinkedList();
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (inDegree[i] == 1)
                queue.offer(i);
        }

        //BFS
        while (!queue.isEmpty()) {
            int size = queue.size();
            List<Integer> currList = new ArrayList();
            for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
                int curr = queue.poll();
                currList.add(curr);

                //add neighbor vertices onto queue
                for (int neighbor : map.get(curr)) 
                    if (--inDegree[neighbor] == 1)
                        queue.offer(neighbor);                
            }
            result = currList;            
        }

        return result;
    }
}
```

