Thoughts:
1. Intuitively, to get a minnimum height tree is to look for the center of the input graph, which is kind of similar to find the mid node of a linked list. To find the mid node of a linked list 
we can cut node from start and end until the list contains only 1 or 2 nodes. 
2. The center of the graph could be 1 node or 2 nodes.(As shown in question description)
3. To find the center of the graph want I will do is
   (1) Cut the leaf (only has one edge)
   (2) check how may nodes left in the graph
   (3) If more than 2 nodes left repeat step (1), otherwise return the nodes left in the graph.
4. The process is shown below.

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/popmao/image_1552674348.png)


With above thoughts my first version code has correct logic but TLE for huge input. Because I created a matrix for the graph which takes too much time to remove the leaves from graph, for each leaf I have to go through
col and row to set the value to 0. Finally I came up with something really similar to Topological Sort using a hashmap to store connected node and a array to store edge count. I will give the accpted code below and fisrt version after that.

```
// Accepted 
public class Solution {
  public List<int> FindMinHeightTrees(int n, int[,] edges) {

    List<int> res = new List<int>();
    if( n == 0 || edges == null) return res;
    int len = edges.GetLength(0);

    //Arrar to store edge count for each node
    int[] edgeCount =  new int[n];

    //Store each node and the connected nodes
    var dict= new Dictionary<int , List<int>>(); 

    for(int i = 0; i < len ; i++)
    {
      int row = edges[i,0];
      int col =edges[i,1];

      // if u, v connected edgeCount[u]++,edgeCount[v]++
      edgeCount[row]++;
      edgeCount[col]++;

      if(dict.ContainsKey(row)){
        dict[row].Add(col);
      }
      else{
        dict.Add(row, new List<int>(){col});
      }

      if(dict.ContainsKey(col)){
        dict[col].Add(row);
      }
      else{
        dict.Add(col, new List<int>(){row});
      }
    }

    while(nodeleftcount(edgeCount) > 2)
    {    

      // Find all leaves
      List<int> leaves = FindLeaves(edgeCount);
      foreach(var leaf in leaves)
      {

          foreach(int e in dict[leaf])
          {
            // For all nodes connected with leaf, edgecount--
            edgeCount[e]--;
          }
          // cut leaf
          edgeCount[leaf] = -1;
      }
    }

    for(int i =0;i<n;i++)
    {
      if(edgeCount[i]>=0)
      {
        res.Add(i);
      }
    }

    return res;
  }


  public int nodeleftcount(int[] isRemoved)
  {
    int count = 0;
    foreach(var i in isRemoved)
    {
      if(i >= 0) count++;
    }
    return count;
  }

  public List<int> FindLeaves(int[] edgeCount)
  {
    List<int> leaves = new List<int>();
    for(int i = 0; i < edgeCount.Length; i++)
    {
        if(edgeCount[i] == 1) leaves.Add(i);
    }
    return leaves;
  }    
}
