![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/yyfyifan/image_1578763185.png)

**That is to say, when a node's parent is knwon, then the subtree rooted at the node is also fixed.** With this in mind, I tried to build a memo to recording a `(node, parent) -> height` map. The graph has O(edges) pairs, and in this tree, edges ~ O(N), so the space complexity is O(N) for this memo. And to rebuild the graph as a adjacency list, it needs O(V+E) space, which is also O(N).

Time: O(N)
Space: O(N)

> Please let me know if this is really a stupid method. I really can't see the 'mid-point' method,so I'm thinking I'm too bad.


